Package io.honeycomb.beeline.tracing.context

Class ThreadLocalTracingContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.honeycomb.beeline.tracing.context.ThreadLocalTracingContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TracingContext

    public class ThreadLocalTracingContext
extends Object
implements TracingContext
    This TracingContext uses a non-static ThreadLocal to store the current tracing stack, which will work under ordinary circumstances to isolate spans associated with a single request from other concurrent requests. Using a non-static ThreadLocal allows for the possibility of having multiple Tracer instances working in the service at the same time, using the same threads, but working on different requests.
